      <abstract id="aspace_cd7a95200a8cce440ca311198915075d">Dr. Edward Tiryakian taught in the
        Department of Sociology from 1965 until his retirement in 2004. He served as Chair of the
        Department in addition to positions as Visiting Professor abroad. He was appointed Director
        for the Center of International Studies in 1988 and served until 1991. The collection
        contains correspondence and materials related to the Dept. of Sociology, and the Center for
        International Studies as well as memoranda, clippings and correspondence regarding general
        University business but also the Nixon Presidential Library controversy and the Allen
        Building Takeover. The collection ranges in date from 1963-2008.</abstract>
      <langmaterial id="aspace_aaaeef7157e543ccef820d36a7db66f4">Material in English</langmaterial>
    </did>
